</tr>
<tr>
<td>two persons</td>
<td>dennek</td>
<td>dekamak</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>two things</td>
<td>dekak</td>
<td>dekamak</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>twice</td>
<td>deparak</td>
<td>dekamak</td>
</tr>
</table>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Vedda_language&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Negation">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Negation">Negation</span></h3>
<p>Another example of simplification in Vedda is minimisations of negative meanings found in Sinhalese:<sup id="cite_ref-D88_31-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-D88-31"><span>[</span>29<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<table class="wikitable">
